Fix binutils zlib build on macOS with Xcode 16.3+.

Xcode 16.3 (macOS Sequoia) predefines TARGET_OS_MAC via Clang, which
triggers binutils' bundled zlib to define fdopen as a macro expanding
to NULL. This conflicts with the system _stdio.h declaration of
fdopen, causing a compile error. The TARGET_OS_MAC guard was meant for
Classic Mac OS (pre-OS X), not modern macOS.

Upstream: https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=32935

--- a/zlib/zutil.h
+++ b/zlib/zutil.h
@@ -137,7 +137,7 @@
 #  endif
 #endif

-#if defined(MACOS) || defined(TARGET_OS_MAC)
+#if defined(MACOS)
 #  define OS_CODE  7
 #  ifndef Z_SOLO
 #    if defined(__MWERKS__) && __dest_os != __be_os && __dest_os != __win32_os
